Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic, transport, and spectroscopic studies for mixtures of isomeric butanediol and N-methyl-2-pyrrolidinone
Citation.sAbstract: The thermodynamic parameters viz. excess molar volume VE and speed of sound u, transport parameter viscosity g, and spectroscopic parameters viz. IR, 1H, 13C NMR have been measured for the mixtures of isomeric butanediol (1,2-, 1,3-, 1,4-, and 2,3-butanediol) and N-methyl-2-pyrrolidinone over the whole composition range at 308.15 K. The partial molar quantities QEi , isentropic compressibility KES , viscosity deviation Dg, deviation in Gibbs free energies of activation for viscous flow g(x), and excess NMR chemical shift dE have been estimated and analyzed. Results show that the interaction between unlike molecules takes place through hydroxyl groups of isomeric butanediol and CO group of N-methyl-2- pyrrolidinone. Excellent agreement between thermodynamic and spectroscopic measurements is observed.
